Verified Purchase

Every year I dread having to deal with Campion.



 



1 out of 5,
            


        reviewed on Feb 14, 2017    



How do they even exist?  It's ridiculous being forced to purchase from a business that clearly hates its customers, and they know we're all trapped with no other option.  I can't think of a single other business that has it so good.  If there were any other bookshop to get this stuff from I would go there.  There used to be a different one that we used to go to.  It was like shopping at Diagon Alley for Hogwarts.  Aisles of every kind of school supply you can imagine and filling our baskets was a joy.  But now there's only Campion.   Where they
Read more 

 make you wait in queues reminiscent of customs in an airport- two queues- and then wait for your name to be called- could be an hour, could be two.  Alternatively you can order the stuff online and receive it in dribs and drabs over the course of term 1.  Sheesh.  There HAS to be a better way!


