Don't use this business, campion book is the worst



 



1 out of 5,
            


        reviewed on Feb 10, 2017    



My son is new to the school, and we had to order some text book from campion.  Then we found out that he was put in an accelerated maths class and he no longer need his current maths book which he hasn't use at all.  However, he fortunately put his name on a sticky tape on top of the book, in which he just peeled it off  and you can see a trace of it which I didn't.  The book is brand new, hasn't use it or anything, I and anyone would have just buy it myself again in that kind of condition anyhow.  So the cashier was doing a refund, she suddenl
Read more 

y said to me in a very unfriendly voice, I can't refund this, it go his name on it.  I just took it from her and rub it and it just came off with no marks or anything, and handed it back to her, but still she won't refund me the money.  So I asked to talk to the manager, she came out, took the book and said no she can't refund it because it got dust and finger marks on it.  I can't believe this, off course it's got fingermarks on it, because we are all holding it.  Then I said I'll clean it and she almost threw the book at me and said if you can clean it I think about it, I just took the tissue and cleaned off the fingerprints and dusts.  And she still doesn't want to refund me, she took it around to her staffs and showed them and said some words to me which weren't polite about would you buy a book like this? Of course I would because it is brand new and hasn't been use, except it have left their shop!!!. I told her that Angus and Robertson wouldn't look at a returned book under a microscope like her, and she said we are not Angus and Robertson are we?  Talking about rude and bad manner , and this comes from a manager can you belive this?..  I wouldn't return a book if it's in bad condition in which they can't resell it, because I know people need to make a living, but this is horrible. Eventually I got the refund, but it just not worth the hassle. I  got two kids still at school for another 8 years or so but I would try to buy anything from Campion for sure.  You can't refund stationery, better get them from Office Work - it's cheaper and you can return easily!!!!


