ed the new books. Week two and they are no-where in sight. Yep, the teacher has started the program and a few of the girls have them. We can't complete homework as we don't have the books nor can my daughter keep up in the class because she DOESNT HAVE THE BOOKS. The school does assist as much as they can however at the end of the day, CAMPION are responsible. Last year I recalled the English book they were reading arrived the last week of term one, the same week they FINISHED THE BOOK IN CLASS. Could I get a refund for the unopened book? No. This year I'm told the maths books are "on their way and now in the hands of Australia Post so not our problem anymore". I do pity the staff having to take these calls, I really do but SOMEONE HAS TO TAKE RESPONSIBILITY. I truly think someone like TODAY TONIGHT have to get into this business and publicly name and shame them. You'd think having the cash in the bank for two months would ensure they have sufficient supply.


