Pathetic client service! They refused to let me speak to a supervisor or manager - so frustrating!!!



 



1 out of 5,
            


        reviewed on Feb 04, 2017    



We are new to this school and just wanted a seamless start for our girls. We didn't want them to have to worry about things like books! Instead their first week has been stressing about exactly that. 

Our daughter came home to tell us that she was the only one in the class without a maths book. I called Campion and was told we had ordered an e-book which was $57.95 which had been sent to us. I said we haven't received it. I was told if we wanted a text book that was $70 which also included the e-book. I said well of course for $12 extra we w
Read more 

ould have both the physical book and the e-book. No that's not possible I was told, as you have been issued with the e-book code. But we have not received it I said so can't we just be sent the book which will also include the e-book? No I was told. You have paid for the e-book and my job is to fulfill your order so I have just emailed you your e-code. I said I don't want to use it if it is going to exclude us from getting the physical book. I was told I could spend an additional $70 to purchase the book. When I said this was crazy and asked whether I could speak to someone else, a supervisor or manager, the person refused. She said there was nothing I could do. She said she worked in a call centre and there were no supervisors. I said surely there was someone at campion that I could speak to. No I was told. I asked there must be a manager at the company that I could speak to or write to. No I was told. I was provided with an email address - sales@campion and was advised that the email would go to the person I was speaking to in any event. 

I still have the email code I was emailed on Tuesday and my daughter has had no Maths book all week. I haven't used the code because I don't want to be excluded from getting the book so my daughter is still yet to do her Maths homework which is due after the weekend. My daughter is very stressed about it.

